  "text": "To understand the computation of the weighted vote, the Tumer-Ghosh model [CITATION_1] for ensemble classifiers will be described. This model defines Added Classification Error as the difference between classifier error and Bayes error, and provides a framework for understanding the reduction in error due to combining. Section 2 explains the computation of the Walsh coefficients, and Section 3 discusses the relationship with the model of Added Classification Error. In Section 4, the weighted vote using Walsh coefficients is compared as the number of nodes and training epochs of MLP base classifiers are systematically varied.",
